	"entries": [
		"You unleash a sweeping wave of black flames in a 30-foot cone. All creatures within the cone must make a Constitution saving throw. A creature takes {@damage 3d8} fire damage and {@damage 3d8} necrotic damage on a failed save or half as much on a successful one. Any creature who fails their saving throw is cursed for 1 minute, suffering disadvantage on attack rolls and ability checks as the lingering black flames weaken their resolve and strength. A creature cursed by this spell can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the curse on itself on a success. A {@spell remove curse} or {@spell dispel magic} spell also ends the curse.",
		"The flames cling to surfaces and remain as dark, flickering embers for the next minute, darkening bright light to dim light and dim light to darkness and imposing disadvantage on Wisdom ({@skill Perception}) checks relying on sight. These magical flames can’t be extinguished by nonmagical means."
